founder of Improved Solutions for Urban Systems Inc., the initial
partner in the program that now includes Dayton Public Schools, the
Rotary Club of Dayton and four area construction trade
associations.
</P>
<P>
   Construction skills aren't the only lessons learned.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's taught me good work habits, like getting to work on time
and having all your tools with you,'' said Ebony Brown, a
17-year-old mother of two.
</P>
<P>
   She said she'll take those habits with her when she studies
cosmetology after she graduates next year from Greene JROTC
Academy, a Dayton school where students got involved in
YouthBuilders during their junior and senior years.
</P>
<P>
   The program also benefits prospective homebuyers.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not rich but I wanted to have a nice house,'' said
homeowner Lori Powers, who had shopped for homes in other areas but
discovered she could only afford a ``two-bedroom crackerbox that
needed repairs.''
</P>
<P>
   Then she found the renovated home on Frank Street. She bought it
for $64,900.
</P>
<P>
   Powers feels she got a lot for her money: a three-bedroom,
two-story home with a full basement where she and her husband Jeff
plan to add another bedroom and a family room.
</P>
<P>
   Helping at-risk youth and helping low-to-moderate income
families was the dual purpose for the program that now has a
waiting list of 200 students.
</P>
<P>
   Now Higdon _ who has a knack for turning her dreams into
realities _ has set her sights on other challenges for the
YouthBuilders team.
</P>
<P>
   With the money raised from selling the Frank Street homes,
YouthBuilders Academy has contracts to buy two more sites: the
dilapidated Rubicon apartment building at Rubicon Drive and Frank
Street, and a downtown building at 224 N. St. Clair St.
</P>
<P>
   ``These will be apartments,'' Higdon said. ``Now the focus is on
downtown development.''
</P>
<P>
   Wendy Hundley writes for the Dayton Daily News, Dayton, Ohio.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
