<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE THURSDAY COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Thursday, June 4, 1998, are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES _ Editor's note: Brief insights from the
editor-in-chief of Cox Newspapers, Arnold Rosenfeld, are now moving
on Mondays for publication Tuesdays. (Rosenfeld, Cox News Service)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ There's a group of us who get together regularly
to discuss the events of the world, the price of watermelons and
whether it'll ever rain again in our lifetime. More importantly, we
talk about the kinds of people we don't like. Such is the
foundation of lasting friendship, to have like enemies. (Murray,
Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   REALLIFE _ Simple things. We seem to be on an endless quest to
