<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-US (Washington) _ President Clinton urges Congress to
approve his decision to renew normal trade relations with China.
But House Majority Leader Richard Armey says approval will be
tougher to get this year because of questions about U.S. technology
transfers to Beijing and alleged Chinese campaign contributions to
the Democrats. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   AIDS-TREATMENT (Washington) _ Women and minority men are more
likely than white men to delay seeking treatment for AIDS and tend
to receive less effective care for the deadly disease, according to
a new study by Johns Hopkins University and the University of
California at San Francisco. By EUN LEE KOH.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-FOOD (Paris) _ already filed _ Tourists coming to France
this year will find that local interest in good food has declined
and that fewer luxury restaurants are open. More and more, the
French are flocking to fast-food places, carryouts, and inexpensive
Asian restaurants. Some experts predict that talented French chefs
will be forced to emigrate. By BERNARD D. KAPLAN.
</P>
