<HEADLINE>
THESE RECIPES ARE REALLY COOL, IN MORE WAYS THAN ONE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Editors know when a big book is coming down the pike. If the
author is a Paula Wolfert, a Patricia Wells or a Madeleine Kamman,
you know the work will be worth considering.
</P>
<P>
   But then there are the cameos, the unexpected surprises of the
publishing world. Just such a one is ``Cool Kitchen: 125 Delicious,
No-Work Recipes for Summertime or Anytime _ No Oven, No Stove, No
Sweat!'' by Lauren Chattman (Morrow, $22).
</P>
<P>
   You'd never know by the ``cookable'' quality of this book that
Chattman is a chef and a first-time author. The recipes are
straight-ahead, light on ingredients and approachably ``outre.''
It's easy to see the pretty plating possibilities of Baja shrimp
salad with avocado dressing (eight ingredients), Cheddar and apple
sandwiches with honey mustard (five ingredients) and goat cheese
wrapped in grape leaves (three ingredients).
</P>
<P>
   This is a great book for those inevitable Texas weekends when
the neighbors are descending, the air-conditioning is working
overtime and the margaritas are calling.
</P>
<P>
   VODKA-SPIKED CHERRY TOMATOES WITH CUMIN-CILANTRO DIPPING SALT
</P>
<P>
   Yields 2 cups
</P>
<P>
   1 pint ripe cherry tomatoes
</P>
<P>
   2/3 cup vodka
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon ground cumin
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons salt
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon finely chopped fresh cilantro leaves
</P>
<P>
   Carefully puncture each cherry tomato in a half-dozen places
with a toothpick. Place tomatoes in a bowl and add the vodka.
Marinate at room temperature, turning tomatoes occasionally, for
2-3 hours.
</P>
<P>
   Combine cumin, salt and cilantro in small bowl. Drain off most
of the vodka from the cherry tomatoes and place in a serving bowl.
(Reserve vodka for making bloody Marys; the vodka already has a
faint tomato flavor.) Serve tomatoes alongside the dipping salt and
with toothpicks.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 19 calories, trace fat, 2
grams carbohydrates, trace protein, 0 milligrams cholesterol, 1,515
milligrams sodium, 10 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   SPINACH SALAD WITH CUCUMBER-FETA DRESSING
</P>
<P>
   Serves 2 as main course, 4 as appetizer
</P>
<P>
   1 medium-size cucumber, peeled, seeded and coarsely chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/4 pound feta cheese, crumbled
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup plain yogurt
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons chopped chives
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon salt, or to taste
</P>
<P>
   1 pound fresh spinach, stemmed, washed and dried
</P>
<P>
   2 medium tomatoes, each cored and cut into 8 wedges
</P>
<P>
   Combine cucumber, feta and yogurt in work bowl of a food
processor. Process until smooth, scraping down the sides of the
bowl once or twice as necessary. Transfer dressing to a small bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Stir chives and salt into dressing.
</P>
<P>
   Combine spinach, tomatoes and dressing in large bowl. Toss until
evenly coated. Divide salad among 4 salad plates. To serve as a
main course, add 3/4 pound of cooked chicken or shrimp and divide
on 2 plates.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 140 calories, 8 grams fat, 11
grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 29 milligrams cholesterol,
574 milligrams sodium, 49 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   MELON AND MANGO WITH YOGURT `CREME FRAICHE'
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   1 cup low-fat yogurt
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup sour cream
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
</P>
<P>
   2 cups cubed honeydew melon, in 1/2-inch pieces
</P>
<P>
   2 cups cubed mango, in 1/2 inches pieces
</P>
<P>
   Combine yogurt, sour cream, sugar and vanilla in small bowl.
Divide fruit among 4 serving bowls. Spoon yogurt mixture over the
fruit. Serve immediately.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 177 calories, 4 grams fat, 34
grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 9 milligrams cholesterol, 55
milligrams sodium, 21 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
