<HEADLINE>
CHIVES ADD ONIONY ZIP TO SALADS, MAIN DISHES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL NUCKOLS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ABCs: These onion relatives have cylindrical, green, mildly
onion-flavored leaves and bluish-purple flowers. Clumps reach 12
inches in height. These perennials are native to Greece, Sweden,
