</P>
<P>
   ``The Herbal Palate Cookbook''
</P>
<P>
   by Maggie Oster and Sal Gilbertie
</P>
<P>
   (Storey, $29.95)
</P>
<P>
   SPINACH AND POTATO CASSEROLE
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4 to 6
</P>
<P>
   4 to 5 medium potatoes, cooked and mashed
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup sour cream
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   Dash pepper
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon granulated sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup butter or margarine
</P>
<P>
   1/4 to 1/2 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons chopped chives
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon dill seed
</P>
<P>
   1 cup cooked, well-drained spinach
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine potatoes, sour cream, salt,
pepper, sugar and butter. Add enough milk to make a fluffy mixture.
Stir in chives, dill seed and spinach. Place in a greased
casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 293 calories, 22 grams fat, 21
grams carbohydrates, 6 grams protein, 16 milligrams cholesterol,
697 milligrams sodium, 66 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Potato Casserole''
</P>
<P>
   by Janet Reeves
</P>
<P>
   (Pelican, $14.95)
</P>
<P>
   CHEESE-CHIVE BISCUITS
</P>
<P>
   Yields about 24 biscuits
</P>
<P>
   2 cups all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon baking powder
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup vegetable shortening
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup grated Cheddar or other sharp cheese
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup chopped fresh chives
</P>
<P>
   1 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons (1/4 stick) butter, melted
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt with a fork.
With a pastry cutter, cut in shortening until the mixture resembles
coarse crumbs. Stir in cheese and chives. Add milk and stir just
until mixture forms a soft dough that pulls away from side of bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead quickly to
mix dough thoroughly. Roll dough out until it is 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out biscuits with a floured biscuit cutter and place on an
ungreased cookie sheet. Brush tops with melted butter and bake
until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 84 calories, 5 grams fat, 8
grams carbohydrates, 2 grams protein, 8 milligrams cholesterol, 219
milligrams sodium, 51 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   ``Cooking With Herbs''
</P>
<P>
   by Emelie Tolley and Chris Mead
</P>
<P>
   (Potter, $24)
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
