<SLUG> BC-HERB-ROSEMARY-1500(2ndTake)-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MEDITERRANEAN FLAVOR ADDS FLAIR TO YOUR SUMMER TABLE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED: chicken or beef.
</P>
<P>
   Note: Mission figs may be substituted for Calimyrnas.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 23 calories, trace fat, 6
grams carbohydrates, trace protein, 0 milligrams cholesterol, 13
milligrams sodium, 2 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Pamela Morgan's Flavors''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   ROSEMARY-OLIVE OATMEAL BATTER BREAD
</P>
<P>
   Yields 1 loaf
</P>
<P>
   2 to 2 1/2 cups unbleached or all-purpose flour
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup old-fashioned rolled oats
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup minced fresh rosemary leaves
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1 package active dry yeast
</P>
<P>
   1 cup water
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup honey
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup canola oil
</P>
<P>
   1 cup pitted, chopped ripe olives
</P>
<P>
   In a large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, oats, rosemary, salt and
yeast, blending well. In a small saucepan, combine water, honey and
oil; heat until hot (120 to 130 degrees). Add liquid to flour
mixture. Using an electric mixer, preferably with a dough hook,
blend at low speed until moistened. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
With mixer on low, beat in olives, then the remaining flour in
1/2-cup increments, until a stiff batter is formed.
</P>
<P>
   Loosely cover batter with plastic wrap sprayed with nonstick
cooking spray. Let rise in a warm place (80 to 85 degrees) about 30
minutes, or until doubled in size.
</P>
<P>
   Spray a 11/2-quart baking dish or 8-by-4-inch or 9-by-5-inch
loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray. Stir batter, then pour into
prepared baking dish or pan. Cover loosely and let rise in a warm
place about 20 minutes, or until batter reaches top of container.
</P>
<P>
   During the last rising, heat oven to 375 degrees. Uncover dough
and bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until loaf is golden brown and sounds
hollow when lightly tapped. Remove loaf from container and cool on
a wire rack.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per slice (12 slices per loaf): 192
calories, 8 grams fat, 28 grams carbohydrates, 4 grams protein, 0
milligrams cholesterol, 319 milligrams sodium, 36 percent of
calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``The Herbal Palate Cookbook'' by Maggie Oster and Sal
Gilbertie (Storey, $29.95)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
