Germany's capital, the federal government plans to order more than
$33 million of freshly painted Neo-Expressionist canvases, cerebral
conceptual installations, neon sculpture and perhaps even earth
works. By Michael Z. Wise. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   FRANKFURT-ARTS (Frankfurt, Germany) _ Frankfurt illustrates all
that's best and worst about the German system of
government-subsidized culture _ a system that in today's economic
landscape is facing the prospect of significant structural change
whether it wants it or not. By Anne Midgette. (Moved).
</P>
