<P>
   ROBERT-KENNEDY-TV (subslug) (Undated) _ The Discovery Channel's
three-hour special ``Robert F. Kennedy: A Memoir'' (beginning
Sunday night at 8), based on Jack Newfield's 1969 book, is about
politics, of course. It's about the Senate racket hearings, the
civil rights movement, presidential campaigns, power plays and the
Vietnam War. But the personal side of Kennedy, who was assassinated
in Los Angeles 30 years ago (June 5, 1968), comes across with just
as much impact. By Anita Gates. (Moved).
</P>
