<TEXT>
<P>
   The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, June 4. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
GOLDWATER-ORATIONS (Tempe, Ariz.) - Former Sen. Barry Goldwater is
remembered by those who served with him and those who followed him
in the United States Congress. We will report the remarks of those
who deliver the key eulogies. By MICHAEL MURPHY. Story will move in
the ``A'' category.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
GOLDWATER-COLOR (Phoenix) - Carolynn Robinson reached out to touch
the red and white stripes on the flag over Barry Goldwater. ``I
wanted to remember that. I wanted to touch a piece of history,''
said the Phoenix woman, one of many mothers who took their children
to visit Trinity Cathedral. We'll talk to others in Tempe inside
and outside Gammage Auditorium - the great and not so great, the
anti-gay protesters and the children waving flags - on Barry M.
Goldwater Rememberance Day. By STEVE YOZWIAK. Story will move in
the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GOLDWATER-FLYBY (Phoenix) - What does it take to get an official
Air Force flyby? By ARIZONA REPUBLIC STAFF. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GOLDWATER-DEMENTIA (Phoenix) - Nancy Reagan, who was in the Phoenix
area Wednesday for Barry Goldwater's funeral, has been in touch
with Susan Goldwater over the past year to participate in what may
have been one of the most exclusive support groups in America.
While their husbands have a connection _ Goldwater was Reagan's
political mentor _ the women also had a separate connection. Both
have served as caregiver second wives to ex-political leaders
suffering from age-related mental dementia. By MAUREEN WEST. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
EXECUTE (Phoenix) - Douglas Gretzler, who confessed to killing 17
people in 21 days in Arizona and California, is scheduled to die
Wednesday afternoon. He's been on death row longer than anyone in
Arizona and will be the first executed during the daytime since the
death penalty was reinstated in AZ. By SUSIE STECKNER and MARK
SHAFFER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
