blame fire ants for the death of 22,000 trout in the Guadalupe
River. Fire ants are toxic to fish. During the ant mating season,
the insects fly and mate in the air, then fall to the ground and
die. When they fell in the river, the fish ate them. By THADDEUS
HERRICK. (Already filed)
