 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; XEROXPARC &LR;  _ Xerox PARC, a fabled research center in the hills
above Palo Alto, is best known for its fumbles. PARC (Palo Alto
Research Center) pioneered the personal computer, the
point-and-click graphical user interface, the laser printer and
Ethernet _ but it never capitalized on them. By Jamie Beckett
