<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-GERMANY-RAILCRASH-NYT, which
moved in ``i'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``There was the silence of the dead. Then we saw about 20 or 30
people who had managed to escape. No one said anything. Then we
heard whimpering and screams.''
</P>
<P>
   _GERHARD BLEYL, among the first to arrive at the site of a train
wreck in Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
