<HEADLINE>
ST. JOHN'S KEEPS JARVIS WAITING 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ While St. John's decides whether hiring a big name
like George Washington's Mike Jarvis as men's basketball coach is
worth the investment _ the Red Storm could acquire one of its other
candidates for half the price _ Jarvis has begun to waver, too.
With his position at George Washington strained because of his
flirtations with other jobs, Jarvis would like to avoid keeping GWU
on hold.
</P>
<P>
   Jarvis earned $600,000 last year and is seeking at least
$800,000 to make the move to St. John's.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jarvis is not going to let it drag on,'' a person close to the
negotiations said. ``At some point, he's going to say, `Take my
name out of the running.'''
</P>
<P>
   Siena's Paul Hewitt, Davidson's Bob McKillop and St.
Bonaventure's Jim Baron were also interviewed for the position last
week. But since the interviews, the coaches have not been
contacted. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
