<SLUG> BC-HKN-CAPITALS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CAPITALS INSISTING HASEK ISN'T MAKING THEM EDGY 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 By TARIK El-BASHIR    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   ODENTON, Md. _ Mind games are a big part of playoff hockey.
</P>
<P>
   Refusing to divulge the status of injured players, changing the
visiting team's practice time without notice and exchanging barbs
through the news media are standard practice in June.
</P>
<P>
   The Washington-Buffalo series has had its fair share of these
trivial pursuits.
</P>
<P>
   But with the four-of-seven-game Eastern Conference finals, which
the Capitals lead, 3-2, shifting to Buffalo for a sixth game on
Thursday, the Sabres have an edge _ the world's best goalie,
Dominik Hasek.
</P>
<P>
   Once again, Hasek stole a game for his team, pulling out a page
from his Olympic diary on Tuesday night at the MCI Center.
</P>
<P>
   Breakdown after defensive breakdown, Hasek saved his team with a
variety of eye-popping stops from almost every position imaginable.
The Sabres were outworked and outplayed by the Capitals and still
won as Hasek, an Olympic gold-medal-winning goalie, stopped 34
shots en route to a 2-1 Sabres victory.
</P>
<P>
   After the game, Sabres Coach Lindy Ruff said he thought that
Hasek might be ``in their heads'' a bit.
</P>
<P>
   Ron Wilson, the Capitals' coach, snapped back, ``He's not in our
heads, trust me.''
</P>
<P>
   But by the middle of the third period, the mounting frustration
could be seen in the faces and reactions of the Washington players
as the Buffalo goalie turned away every puck hurled in his
direction.
</P>
<P>
   Hasek stopped the Capitals' sniper, Peter Bondra, not once, but
twice, on breakaways.
</P>
<P>
   Two times, Hasek closed the door on Adam Oates, who was standing
on Hasek's doorstep with the puck on his stick and a wide-open net
staring him in the face.
</P>
<P>
   Joe Juneau, too, was foiled by Hasek from point-blank range.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had a couple of casual moments around the net,'' Wilson
said, ``and with Dominik you can't be casual. You can't think, `I
have an empty net, I'll make this one pretty.'''
</P>
<P>
   It was surely Hasek's best game of the tournament, and was
probably one the Sabres had no business winning.
</P>
<P>
   Hasek's show-stopping performance left the Capitals deflated. It
left their coach exasperated.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to play the same way we did yesterday,'' Wilson
said Wednesday after some of the Capitals practiced at the team's
facility outside Annapolis. ``If we play like that, I like our
chances. But if you can't score on Dominik, then there is not much
we can do. We have to find a way to put the puck past Dominik. He's
a great goalie.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-03-98 2224EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
